prcedure_miss_data_explain: This study collects and analyses blood glucose levels at set time points during study sessions. Timers and alarms are used to minimise the risk of missing data during data collection. In the event of a missed timepoint, the blood glucose level is checked at the earliest possible time and the time taken recorded. If within 5 mins of next timepoint, the sample is marked as missed and the next sample collected at the appropriate time.
